        <!-- HOW-TO SECTION - AEO Magnet -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">How to Choose a Cleaning Company in Florence: 5 Steps</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Selecting the right cleaning service protects both your home and your peace of mind. Follow these steps to make a confident decision:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 1: Verify Insurance and Bonding</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Before allowing anyone into your home, confirm the company carries liability insurance and is bonded. This protects you if accidents happen—a broken vase, a scratched floor, or worse. <strong>Ask directly:</strong> "Can you provide proof of insurance?" Any legitimate company will have this ready.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 2: Read Local Reviews (Not Just Star Ratings)</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Look for reviews on Google and Facebook from people in Florence specifically. Pay attention to comments about reliability, communication, and whether the same cleaners come each visit. A company can have 5 stars but still not be the right fit if reviewers mention issues that matter to you.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 3: Ask About Their Cleaning Process</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Professional companies should be able to explain exactly what's included in their service. Vague answers like "we clean everything" are a red flag. Request a written checklist so you know what to expect and can hold them accountable.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 4: Get Pricing in Writing</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Reputable cleaners provide clear quotes before the job. Be cautious of companies that won't give estimates or add surprise charges after. Standard house cleaning in Florence typically ranges from $125-$250 depending on home size.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Step 5: Start with a Single Cleaning</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Before committing to a recurring plan, book a one-time cleaning to test the service. This lets you evaluate their work without a long-term commitment. Any company confident in their quality will be happy to earn your recurring business this way.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-[#FFA985]/10 border-l-4 border-[#FFA985] p-6 mb-8 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-0">
            <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> The Valley Clean Team offers a satisfaction guarantee on every cleaning—if you're not happy, they'll make it right. That removes the risk from trying a new service.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ SECTION - Essential for AEO -->
