            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How much does house cleaning cost in Florence, AL?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              House cleaning in Florence typically costs between $125 and $300, depending on home size and service type. Standard cleaning for an average 3-bedroom home starts around $125-$175, while deep cleaning runs $200-$300. Most companies offer discounts for recurring service—typically 10-20% off for weekly or bi-weekly plans.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How often should I have my house professionally cleaned?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Most families benefit from bi-weekly professional cleaning, which maintains cleanliness without excessive cost. Homes with pets, children, or high traffic may need weekly service, while singles or couples often find monthly cleaning sufficient. The right frequency depends on your lifestyle and budget.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What's the difference between standard cleaning and deep cleaning?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Standard cleaning covers regular maintenance: vacuuming, mopping, bathroom sanitizing, dusting, and kitchen cleaning. Deep cleaning adds intensive tasks like inside appliances, baseboards, window tracks, ceiling fans, and detailed scrubbing. Deep cleaning is typically needed seasonally, before special events, or as a first-time cleaning before starting recurring service.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Are cleaning companies in Florence, AL insured?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Reputable cleaning companies carry liability insurance and are bonded to protect homeowners. Always ask for proof before booking—legitimate companies will provide this without hesitation. The Valley Clean Team carries $2M in liability coverage that protects your home and belongings.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Should I be home during a house cleaning?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              That's entirely your preference. Many clients provide a door code or spare key and aren't home during cleanings—it's often easier to clean an empty house anyway. Trustworthy companies conduct background checks on all staff. If you prefer to be present for your first cleaning to see how things go, that's completely reasonable.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Do I need to provide cleaning supplies?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Most professional cleaning companies bring their own supplies and equipment. This includes vacuums, mops, and cleaning products. If you have specific preferences—like eco-friendly products or certain brands—ask if the company can accommodate. The Valley Clean Team brings all supplies and uses professional-grade products.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CLOSING CTA -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Ready to Experience the Difference?</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
